[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Face to face recruitment at public launch events 
[normal]was
[normal] really successful, particularly where women can meet coaches/leaders and other participants, and see example activity sessions in action.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]E
[normal]xisting participants
[normal] were encouraged
[normal] to bring their friend
[normal]s and/or link with existing groups and organisations in the community so women 
[normal]could
[normal] 
[normal]take part with people they kn
[normal]e
[normal]w and 
[normal]were
[normal] 
[normal]comfortable with.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]E
[normal]asy-to-access practical information about what sessions will entail
[normal] was important, as was 
[normal]r
[normal]eassuring women that other participants 
[normal]would
[normal] 
[normal]also be beginners.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Keeping women interested in sport
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Minimising potential practical barriers by offering: convenient session times, accessible venue locations, links to childcare facilities, flexible drop-in 
[normal]sessions and affordable prices.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Encouraging and motivating women to take part – frequent contact from project staff (e.g. email updates, follow up contact with women who haven’t attended for a while), social atmosphere, fun and non-competitive sessions, fr
[normal]iendly and welcoming coaches/leaders and incentives (e.g. loyalty schemes).
