[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Section Four[bold]: Sport[bold] Governance[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Sport England and UK Sport have set out a joint expectation within t
[normal]he 13-17 governance funding requirements that boards should be at least 25
[normal]%
[normal] women by 2017
[normal]. 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Both bodies are jointly monitoring progress to this through 
[normal]our
[normal] joint audit and assurance process. 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Women’s Sport and Fitness Foundation 
[normal]ha
[normal]s
[normal] 
[normal]been commissioned t
[normal]o carry out 
[normal]an
[normal] 
[normal]annual survey of women on boards
[normal]. 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Sport England is also drawing together a pool of high calibre individuals 
[normal]who 
[normal]have expressed an interest in being on NGB boards, and we highlight advertised roles to those individuals
[normal]. 
